features: UNIQUE TAPERED BRISTLES: Toothbrushes feature tapered bristles that reach between teeth and around the gums to gently massage the gums, super soft toothbrushes for adults gently and effectively clean the gum line, without causing injury of gums

28 HOLES BRUSH HEADS DESIGN: Dividing the dense bristles into 28 holes, the unique spacing dries faster than the normal one and prevents things from getting trapped at the roots, helping to keep your toothbrush clean. In addition, we recommend that you rinse the brush head after your teeth have been cleaned, which can better keep your toothbrush in a better condition.

PORTABLE TOOTHBRUSH: Each soft toothbrush is individually packaged. This ensures that the toothbrush is well protected. In Addition to this, Apical Life toothbrush packs are perfect for travel, camping, business trips and people on the go. This makes them very convenient for everyday use.

5 PACK OF WIDE BRUSH HEADS: The brush heads are a little wider than the regular size to cover more teeth and clean them better, which is perfect for adults. With 5 brushes in this value pack, there are enough for every member of the family, and you can even set aside a few for travel brushes.

ERGONOMIC HANDLE: This manual toothbrush is ergonomically designed with a shape and grip with silicone strips for maximum control while brushing and provides a comfortable grip that makes a difference when brushing.Apical Life carefully designs toothbrushes to enhance your quality of life

manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: Better Oral Care & Durable bristles Leaving space between each bunch of bristles, allows the bristles to dry faster after use and prevents things from getting trapped at the roots, helping to keep your toothbrush clean. Thoroughly Clean and Effective The brush head is a bit wider than regular size (close to 1.5X wider ) which can cover more tooth and improve the cleaning effectiveness. Unique Tapered Bristles Penetrates deep between the teeth and around the gums, gently massaging the gums with no pain or bleeding. Ideal for those with sensitive teeth, receding gums, braces and after gum treatment.

Enough To Use According to the dentist's recommendation, toothbrushes should be replaced every 3 months for better oral hygiene Ergonomic Handle Apical Life soft toothbrush features an ergonomic handle and an angled, compact brush head that helps remove stains and plaque from hard-to-reach back teeth Open Box Illustration First, you need to press down around the buckle so that you can open the toothbrush box more easily, and then open the buckle.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 17, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars very soft but effective
reviews.reviewText: I needed a very, very soft toothbrush for some gum sensitivity and recession issues. This toothbrush was just what I needed! It's soft but it cleans teeth and gums well. I like that the bristle area is broad; makes it easier to get to all surfaces. The travel cases are great - very sturdy yet light. I'll buy these again!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 5, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars I was looking for a soft tooth brush and I found the best
reviews.reviewText: I don't write to many review but the Apical Life Ultra Soft Toothbrushes are just outstanding, not just for their value but for what they are and do. First off, This tooth brush is a hidden gem. Having searched for a long time and having tried all the big name brands and some non-name brands claiming to be soft, I finally found these buried in the Amazon pages. I tried these out for 2 weeks before leaving this review and all I can say is that for a set of 5 brushes, these are outstanding and top all competitors by far. If you want a tooth brush that gets the job done without damaging your gums, these are it. 5 brushes for ~$10 is just insane. Kudos to all those who made and distributed these fine brushes.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 19, 2023
reviews.reviewText: My kids love these toothbrushes, sensitive gums is a trait that my kids got from me. So little did I know, it was the reason they hated brushing their teeth. So when they woke up with these babies under there pillows from the tooth fairy 🧚🏽‍♀️ aka mom ( when a child looses a tooth in my house, all the kids get new toothbrushes, floss, mouthwash etc. instead of money. They also know mom is the tooth fairy) my kids each came to me one by one to tell me how soft their new toothbrush is and how comfortable it feels in comparison to the "soft" bristle brushes. They love brushing their teeth now, and have turned it into an event, they remind each other its time to brush and the 4 of them all venture into the bathroom together to brush and make sure the younger siblings brush correctly. It's music to my ears to hear them enjoy an activity they once dreaded.
